reviews.reviewText: My one and a half year old great granddaughter loves to play with them. Lots of giggles.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The cutest little cars ever!
reviews.reviewText: I was not prepared for the level of cuteness that came out of this box! Cannot wait for my son to open them for Christmas! They seem well made, cannot speak for long-lastingness, but for the price I am over the moon!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is an odd combination of little cars. There are two cars that are made for younger children, like 9+ months. There is a little plastic box with a lid that holds smaller cars, and these are definitely not safe for babies. I let my 9- and 12-month-old grandchildren play with the bigger cars, but they do have wheels that look as if they could come off in a baby's mouth and cause choking. They are what I usually stick in their hands while I change a diaper. One of the bigger car's has a "tow" on it and it came off when I accidentally stepped on it. I just threw the tow away, as it was also another choking hazard. Overall, I think these are best suited for children 3-years or older. I rated this collection four stars (and that's probably generous) because it should be two separate products.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I've found that I love these kind of pull back cars the best. My son loves all cars, but he gets bored with cars that don't "go fast" so these pull back ones are perfect as they really can move quite quickly. They are a nice size for toddler hands too - not so big they can't grasp them, but big enough you aren't worried they will eat the wheels randomly. Overall, fun toy - could make a great gift too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great car set
reviews.reviewText: My 20 month old has been playing with these little cars for a couple months now and he really loves them. He's currently more into the 2 larger cars than the smaller ones but I love that both are included as Im sure he will grow into loving the smaller ones as he gets a little older. Great quality

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute, well made
reviews.reviewText: These are a really cute set of cars. I like that there is a variety of colors (sometimes cars only come in “boy” colors but these have pinks and purples too) they pull back and drive really easily and nicely. I like that they have moving parts (like the cement mixer barrel etc) I also find them to be versatile because of the sizes. The bigger cars are nice for my baby (especially with the bell inside) and the smaller ones are great for my toddler. They would also make for really nice goody bag fillers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are adorable!
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these to give to my two youngest grandchildren and I'm so pleased with how cute they are! There are six smaller ones and two a bit larger. The larger ones are pastel colored and have eyes that move when you push them forward and a soft, pliable silicone type material on the top that little ones can easily chew on. The six smaller ones are more vibrant in color with four of them (not the pink or red ones) having moving parts in addition to the wheels. In my opinion, these would be an excellent gift for any car loving toddler.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These are fun for young kids, my toddler grandson enjoys them, and they're all over the house at this point. I have hard floors, so there's plenty of space for him to play with them, but they do work on shorter piled area rug type carpets. I don't know if they'd work on regular carpet, the cars might just go slower? A good assortment of cars, he has these pigeon holed around the house, and always seems to pop up with one.
